  @skip
  Scenario Outline: [6] Comparing lists to lists
    Given an empty graph
    When executing query:
      """
      RETURN <lhs> = <rhs> AS result
      """
    Then the result should be, in any order:
      | result   |
      | <result> |
    And no side effects

    Examples:
      | lhs           | rhs           | result |
      | [1, 2]        | [1]           | false  |
      | [null]        | [1]           | null   |
      | ['a']         | [1]           | false  |
      | [[1]]         | [[1], [null]] | false  |
      | [[1], [2]]    | [[1], [null]] | null   |
      | [[1], [2, 3]] | [[1], [null]] | false  |

  Scenario Outline: [7] Comparing maps to maps
    Given an empty graph
    When executing query:
      """
      RETURN <lhs> = <rhs> AS result
      """
    Then the result should be, in any order:
      | result   |
      | <result> |
    And no side effects

    Examples:
      | lhs             | rhs                | result |
      | {}              | {}                 | true   |
      | {k: true}       | {k: true}          | true   |
      | {k: 1}          | {k: 1}             | true   |
      | {k: 1.0}        | {k: 1.0}           | true   |
      | {k: 'abc'}      | {k: 'abc'}         | true   |
      | {k: 'a', l: 2}  | {k: 'a', l: 2}     | true   |
      | {}              | {k: null}          | false  |
      | {k: null}       | {}                 | false  |
      | {k: 1}          | {k: 1, l: null}    | false  |
      | {k: null, l: 1} | {l: 1}             | false  |
      | {k: null}       | {k: null, l: null} | false  |
      | {k: null}       | {k: null}          | null   |
      | {k: 1}          | {k: null}          | null   |
      | {k: 1, l: null} | {k: null, l: null} | null   |
      | {k: 1, l: null} | {k: null, l: 1}    | null   |
      | {k: 1, l: null} | {k: 1, l: 1}       | null   |

